Midnight Commander (mc)
visual, dual-pane file manager
  https://midnight-commander.org/
  https://github.com/MidnightCommander/

mcedit
full-featured text editor with syntax highlighting support
embedded into mc

-------------------------------------------------------------
Resources location

mc Skin Editor
  https://skins.midnight-commander.org/

system's mcedit syntax highlighting files are placed in dir:
  /usr/share/mc/syntax

user's mcedit syntax highlighting files are placed in dir:
  ~/.local/share/mc/syntax

-------------------------------------------------------------
Hints

mcedit highlighter regular expression's syntax is
non-standard, and is poorely documented. Some info is below:

mcedit    PCRE2's equivalent
[a-c]     \[a-c\]    (no special meaning of [ ])
\[a-c\]   (a|-|c)*   (no special meaning of -  )
{a-c}     \{a-c\}    (no special meaning of { })
\{a-c\}   [ac-]      (no special meaning of -  )
.         \.
(         \(
)         \)
*         .*
+         [^ \t]*
?         \?
\*        \*
\+        \+
^         \^
$         \$
|         \|
\s        [ ]        (space only)
\t        \t
\n        \n

Pressing C-s twice effectively reloads the syntax file (so
you don't have to exit the editor, or MC itself, to test
your syntax modifications).

References:
[1] https://github.com/MidnightCommander/mc/issues/3734
